headline: Estée Lauder Flags $100 Million Tariff Alarm
summary: Estee Lauder Companies, Inc. (NYSE:EL) reported stronger-than-expected quarterly results on Thursday, driven by broad-based demand across regions and categories across its prestige beauty portfolio. The company also highlighted progress on its global restructuring plan, including significant job cuts, and delivered a more confident outlook, even as shares traded lower ahead of the open.
